spanGrp.span: Where there was a small house, there lived a seal.
M t m estee j kajki r yuliski jrga jeska foka sr-g e-gla
er jie dul j jr sig
then the phone rang and he answered.
er esteee telefono buran' er jie t kontestar-w
The female mouse called him and he told him lets go for a ride.
er esteee koo (_) koo estee busi n t chag er jie t (_) er sh-ite Banra se shk esteee yul
So he got ready put his hat on, grabbed the keys and left.
er jie jk alistar-w t sombrero jiw jie t estee yabe gug-w mn-m
Then he got where the female mouse was at the side waiting for him.
deu-m-ra estee koo yaba esteee busi je dul k ska t kikse-g
Off they went; on the road they saw a frog playing with a ball
er mn-lo-m m ala inga estee sapo daj-te estee bola wa je jin-g
and their car crashed against a stone,
er mn jie-wa jie-wa mn-lo-m-te estee jak m karro p
turned over, and the frog saw that the seal was dead.
er bolk-w-nu-m er esteee foka eee (_) sapo t s'-ra d-w
He saw how his soul went up in the air but they managed to grab it;
er s-ite-ra alma mn jui estee (_) esteee siw' inga er jie-wa t gug-w
when he saw that the mouse was on a branch and came down,
er esteee m s'-ite-ra estee koo (_) yaba busi je (_) kal m esteee (_) estee kaljula inga Jeska er jie jaw-te
he/she saw that the seal was dead;
so they called the ambulance and put him in it.
er jie-wa t ambulansia chag je jrga pakk-w-ite er mntse w
The frog remained there and cried a lot.
M sapo je (_) je jatan-w jin-g k
Meanwhile he saw the seal was coming on crutches
er je batamra s'-ite-ra foka daj (m) pero je daj r muleta inga
and ran fast and brought a bed and put him on it
er estee m tun' b' t m jaka bete w je inga m'w-ite
put a blanket on the ground and the seal lay down;
er m esteee kobija tulka-ite jiski inga er foka t jk m'w
the frog fetched food and gave it to him and saw that the seal got well;
er m d-te wal shk w je m'-ite er (hm) esteee s'-ite-ra foka je estee je bin'-ka-ra
so he took off the bandage;
the seal stood up and saw that the car was not there,
er foka jk d-ka er ya jie t s-ra (extra) ka karro ju-n
so they went to look for it;
er (_) k-lu-m k-lu-m (_) estee (_) estee ala inga
then they stopped and saw that the female mouse was driving the car, which was already fixed.
er jk dach er jie-wa t s'-ra (_) estee koo yaba je wa estee karro dats' era karro bi-n'-w
So they all, the mouse, the seal and the frog, went for a ride.
era/ er esteee karro inga (_) jie-wa mn-lo-m estee pasear-w koo jam esteee foka estee sapo je mn-lo-m pasear-w
The female drove the car; it was ok again.
era estee ko este koo este karro mnts' bin'-ka-n estabagl
